Trump: "...when I watch him...walk out of a store...and he's walking..with a...ice cream...and the question the media asks him 'what kind of ice cream what flavour ice cream do you have...and he's in the midst of a scandal.."
...FUCKING WHAT? What the actual fuck was that? Where the fuck were you going with that, you complete fucking moron??? I mean seriously, draw the rest of us a diagram...for fuck's sake..
Okay (Deep breath) so yeah, let's try to process this absolute clusterfuck of a statement:
Trump apparently wants us to believe that he goes out to stores like a 'normal' person does, when he definitely gets somebody else to do it for him, some underling or butler or whatever. I'm disregarding the fact that if he actually did, he would be surrounded by secret service, absolutely everybody in the store would have been background checked already, oh and it would be a logistical nightmare for a shameless photo opportunity. I personally find this highly unlikely, kind of in the realms of 'would never happen' but I digress...
During this already unbelievably hypothetical scenario, he see's Joe Biden walking out of a store, yep he's walking on two feet no less, no shuffling or waddling or whatever the fuck Trump does for locomotion, I felt this was worth mentioning because Trump himself mentioned it twice. Perhaps with amazement but my suspicion is that it's envy.
So Joe's evidently carrying ice cream. I've never once seen anyone do this as it's guaranteed to start melting it and it's absurdly cold, which is why people tend to put ice cream in bags or any other possible way to avoid carrying it...kind of implying that Trump has absolutely no idea, not a single clue, on how people purchase ice cream...
Anyway moving on, seemingly from out of nowhere, the media gets hold of Joe on the way back to his car, like they do, and repetitively start asking him what flavour ice cream it is, because media vans love to waste their time hanging out at malls in an attempt to ambush politicians explicitly so they can ask them what they have bought. No Donald..no they don't do that...you twit.
Still with me so far? I'm quite impressed! We're now onto the climax of this story, the Grand Finale! The masterstroke in the art of Donald's storytelling!
